The City Traffic Department is facing a high number of accidents at intersections and highways caused by unpredictable traffic patterns, poorly timed traffic signals, and unsafe road conditions. Currently, there is no intelligent system available to predict or provide early warnings about accident-prone areas. This results in delayed preventive actions, increased emergency response costs, and risks to public safety. Therefore, there is a need to develop a machine learning–based traffic accident risk prediction system that can accurately identify high-risk zones in advance while minimizing false alarms.
